ation reports, findings docs) go under `.ddx/executions/20260515T104757-0ab57b74/` (the per-attempt evidence directory under `.ddx/executions/`). **Never write reports to `/tmp` or any path outside the repository** — out-of-repo paths are invisible to the post-merge reviewer and cause BLOCK on missing evidence. If the bead names a specific in-repo path, use it; else default to `.ddx/executions/20260515T104757-0ab57b74/\u0026lt;short-name\u0026gt;.md`. Stage and commit the report alongside code.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Mode and overrides\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;DDX_MODE=bead_execution: edit code/docs for bead AC. Only broad queue-steward default is overridden; tracker, merge-policy, verification, safety stay active. Bead description/AC override CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, and project defaults.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Review gate\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- The review is a gate, not an escape hatch — meet every AC in this pass.\u0026#xA;- Address every BLOCKING `\u0026lt;review-findings\u0026gt;` item; do not declare `no_changes` with blocking findings open.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Constraints\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Work only inside this execution worktree.\u0026#xA;- Keep `.ddx/executions/` intact — DDx uses it as execution evidence.\u0026#xA;- **Never run `ddx init`** — the workspace is initialized; running it corrupts the bead queue.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s named scope.\u0026#xA;- Do not rewrite CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, or other project-instructions files unless the bead asks.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## When the work is done\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;After the commit succeeds and every AC is verified, stop. Return control to the orchestrator — do not keep exploring or testing.\n  \u003c/instructions\u003e\n  \u003cbead id=\"ddx-689471d1\"\u003e\n    \u003ctitle\u003ereadiness: accept model-output waiver and child-acceptance variants\u003c/title\u003e\n    \u003cdescription\u003e\nPROBLEM\u0026#xA;`ddx work --watch --harness codex --model gpt-5.4 --project /Users/erik/Projects/fizeau` still reports readiness decode failures and then fail-opens into execution. Two observed shapes are now known:\u0026#xA;- `waivers_applied` may be emitted as a flat string list, causing `json: cannot unmarshal string into Go struct field preClaimReadinessClassificationPromptResult.waivers_applied of type agent.preClaimReadinessWaiver`.\u0026#xA;- `suggested_child_beads[].acceptance` may be emitted as a single string, causing `json: cannot unmarshal string into Go struct field preClaimReadinessSuggestedChild.suggested_child_beads.acceptance of type []string`.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Both failures make the readiness model unavailable even though the model produced a semantically usable classification. This keeps readiness from contributing route/difficulty signals and produces noisy fail-open logs during normal `ddx work --watch` operation.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;ROOT CAUSE WITH FILE:LINE\u0026#xA;`cli/internal/agent/preclaim_intake_hook.go:60-72` decodes the readiness classification payload directly into strict Go structs. `preClaimReadinessClassificationPromptResult.SuggestedChildren` is `[]preClaimReadinessSuggestedChild`, while `preClaimReadinessSuggestedChild.Acceptance` at `cli/internal/agent/preclaim_intake_hook.go:148-152` requires `[]string`. `WaiversApplied` at `cli/internal/agent/preclaim_intake_hook.go:71` requires structured objects. `decodeReadinessClassificationPayloadWithMode` at `cli/internal/agent/preclaim_intake_hook.go:584-588` fails the whole readiness classification on any JSON shape mismatch. The prompt text at `cli/internal/agent/preclaim_intake_hook.go:424-431` asks for `suggested_child_beads` and `waivers_applied` but does not give enough defensive handling for common model scalar/list variants.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;PROPOSED FIX\u0026#xA;Add small JSON normalization types for readiness model-only fields so decoding accepts the observed variants without creating new execution paths. Specifically: normalize `waivers_applied` from omitted/null/empty array/flat string list/object list, and normalize `suggested_child_beads[].acceptance` from either a string or a string array. Keep the internal readiness result behavior unchanged unless existing code already consumes these fields. Tighten the readiness prompt so it documents the preferred shapes and explicitly says scalar fallbacks are tolerated only by the decoder.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;NON-SCOPE\u0026#xA;Do not persist readiness waiver or child-bead suggestion data to bead metadata. Do not add numeric difficulty/score metadata. Do not implement automatic decomposition behavior here. Do not change the easy/medium/hard routing contract.\n    \u003c/description\u003e\n    \u003cacceptance\u003e\n1. Add `TestPreClaimReadiness_DecodesWaiversAppliedStringList` proving payloads with `\u0026#34;waivers_applied\u0026#34;:[\u0026#34;none\u0026#34;]` decode successfully and preserve the readiness outcome.\u0026#xA;2. Add `TestPreClaimReadiness_DecodesWaiversAppliedObjectList` proving the existing structured waiver-object form still decodes.\u0026#xA;3. Add `TestPreClaimReadiness_DecodesSuggestedChildAcceptanceString` proving payloads with `\u0026#34;suggested_child_beads\u0026#34;:[{\u0026#34;title\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;Split docs\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;acceptance\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;1. TestFoo passes\\n2. cd cli \u0026amp;\u0026amp; go test ./internal/agent/... green\u0026#34;}]` decode successfully and preserve the readiness outcome.\u0026#xA;4. Add `TestPreClaimReadiness_DecodesSuggestedChildAcceptanceList` proving the documented string-array child acceptance form still decodes.\u0026#xA;5. Add or update prompt coverage, suggested `TestPreClaimReadinessPromptSpecifiesOutputShapes`, proving the readiness prompt explicitly documents `waivers_applied` and `suggested_child_beads[].acceptance` shapes.\u0026#xA;6. Existing `TestPreClaimReadiness_DecodesFractionalScore` remains green.\u0026#xA;7. `cd cli \u0026amp;\u0026amp; go test ./internal/agent/... -run \u0026#34;TestPreClaimReadiness_.*(Waiver|SuggestedChild|FractionalScore)|TestPreClaimReadinessPromptSpecifiesOutputShapes\u0026#34; -count=1` passes.\u0026#xA;8. `lefthook run pre-commit` passes.\n    \u003c/acceptance\u003e\n    \u003clabels\u003earea:agent, area:readiness, area:routing, kind:bug, phase:2, downstream:fizeau\u003c/labels\u003e\n    \u003cmetadata base-rev=\"cfaaab932bc2230097b0a8628eb8ba5164427317\" bundle=\".ddx/executions/20260515T104757-0ab57b74\"/\u003e\n  \u003c/bead\u003e\n  \u003cgoverning\u003e\n    \u003cnote\u003eNo governing references were pre-resolved. The bead description above is the primary contract. If it names files, specs, or prior beads, read those before editing. Ground decisions in what is already in the repository; do not guess.\u003c/note\u003e\n  \u003c/governing\u003e\n\u003c/execute-bead\u003e\n","metadata":{"DDX_MODE":"bead_execution","attempt_id":"20260515T104757-0ab57b74","base_rev":"cfaaab932bc2230097b0a8628eb8ba5164427317","bead_id":"ddx-689471d1","bundle_path":".ddx/executions/20260515T104757-0ab57b74","correlation_id":"ddx-689471d1:20260515T104757-0ab57b74","prompt_file":".ddx/executions/20260515T104757-0ab57b74/prompt.md","prompt_sha":"ac872b3b1c36e7cb406aa33daa90ac7245eb53d31d2f64a455350cc84b7a5b20","role":"implementer","session_id":"eb-1612174f","worker_id":""}}}
